    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-08T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="860"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d860">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">681.003/122: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-08T16:00:00+00:00"
                            >January 8, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 8—1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. My telegram No. 3, January 7, 1 p.m.<note n="93" xml:id="d860fn93">Not
                        printed.</note> Following submission of formal protests today as directed in
                    the Department’s 65, December 15, 2 p.m.,<note n="94" xml:id="d860fn94">
                        <ref target="frus1934v02#pg_874">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1934, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 874</ref>.</note> No. 66, December 20,
                    8 p.m.,<note n="95" xml:id="d860fn95">
                        <ref target="frus1934v02#pg_880">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 880</ref>.</note> and 68, December 29,
                    3 p.m.,<note n="96" xml:id="d860fn96">
                        <ref target="frus1934v02#pg_883">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 883</ref>.</note> conference took place
                    with all Moroccan experts of Foreign Office.</p>
                <p>Subsecretary states no agreement yet come to with France concerning proposed new
                    customs regime Morocco.<note n="97" xml:id="d860fn97">For correspondence
                        relating to French proposals for a new customs regime, see <ref
                            target="#pg_951">pp. 951</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Foreign Office ready to enter into full and friendly examination of 1928
                        claims<note n="98" xml:id="d860fn98">See <ref target="frus1928v03#pg_344">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1928, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, pp. 344</ref> ff.</note> and recognition
                    of Spanish Zone conferences will probably begin tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
